A Kano High Court has nullified the election of a House of Assembly Member under the All Progressives Congress (APC) platform, Magaji Dahiru Zarewa. The court sacked Zarewa and declared Jibril Isma’il Falgore of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) as the elected member, representing Rogo federal constituency, saying he failed to resign from his position as the managing director of the Kano Drugs and Consumables Supply Agency 30 days to the election. It further directed the state Assembly Clerk to swear-in Falgore as the legitimate member for Rogo constituency immediately. With this development, the ruling PDP now has 13 members while the ruling APC has 27 members in the Kano State House of Assembly.